  <static seed="40" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/DivideFractions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Divide: <m>\displaystyle{ \frac{3}{5} \div \frac{4}{3} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{9}{20}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>When we do division with fractions, as with</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{3}{5} \div \frac{4}{3} }</m></p>
<p>we first change division to multiplication, and at the same time flip the second fraction. In this case, we have</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{3}{5} \cdot \frac{3}{4} }</m></p>
<p>Then we do fraction multiplication as usual. The full process is:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
    \frac{3}{5} \div \frac{4}{3}
        \amp = \frac{3}{5} \cdot \frac{3}{4} \\
        \amp = \frac{3 \cdot 3}{5 \cdot 4} \\
        \amp = \frac{9}{20}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
